    <div class="popup-content">
        <h2>Footstep Power Generator Using Piezoelectric Technology.</h2><br>
        <p><h3>Overview</h3></p>
        <p>This project is designed to generate electrical energy from human footsteps using piezoelectric sensors. It converts mechanical pressure from walking into usable electrical energy, promoting a sustainable and eco-friendly power solution.</p>
        <br>
        <p><h3>Project Description</h3></p>
        <p>The system works on the principle of the piezoelectric effect, where mechanical stress applied to sensors produces electrical energy. When a person steps on the platform, pressure is applied to the sensors, generating voltage.


        This generated energy is then converted into usable form and stored for powering small electrical devices such as LED lights. The project demonstrates an innovative way of utilizing wasted human energy efficiently.</p>
    
        <br>
        <ul>
        <li>Software: SolidWorks</li>
        <li>Technology: Piezoelectric</li>
        <li>Type: Prototype</li>
        <li>Role: Design + Fabrication</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <p><h3>Key Features</h3></p>
        <ul>
        <li>Converts foot pressure into electrical energy</li>
        <li>Eco-friendly and renewable energy source</li>
        <li>Simple and cost-effective system</li>
        <li>Suitable for continuous energy generation</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <p><h3>Advantages</h3></p>
        <ul>
        <li>Reduces dependency on conventional energy sources</li>
        <li>Utilizes wasted human energy</li>
        <li>Low maintenance</li>
        <li>Supports smart city development </li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <p><h3>Applications</h3></p>
        <ul>
        <li>Railway stations</li>
        <li>Shopping malls</li>
        <li>Footpaths and walkways</li>
        <li>Public places with high foot traffic</li>
        </ul>


    </div>
    </div>


