    <h2>Three-Wheel Half Bike – Design and Fabrication</h2><br>
        <p><h3>Overview</h3></p>
        <p>This project involves the design and fabrication of a three-wheel half bike, combining stability, efficiency, and innovative vehicle structure. The aim is to create a compact and balanced vehicle suitable for safe and smooth transportation.</p>
        <br>
        <p><h3>Project Description</h3></p>
        <p>The three-wheel half bike is designed by integrating a two-wheeler front section with a single rear wheel or modified chassis structure to improve balance and control. The design focuses on reducing instability commonly found in conventional two-wheelers. <br>

The fabrication process includes chassis modification, frame design, wheel alignment, and proper mounting of components. Special attention is given to weight distribution and structural strength to ensure durability and safety.</p>
    
    <br>
        <ul>
        <li>Software: FUSION 360</li>
        <li>Technology: Vehicle Design, Fabrication, Mechanical Systems</li>
        <li>Type: Prototype</li>
        <li>Role: Design + Fabrication</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <p><h3>Key Features</h3></p>
        <ul>
        <li>Three-wheel configuration for improved stability</li>
        <li>Enhanced balance compared to two-wheelers</li>
        <li>Compact and lightweight design</li>
        <li>Suitable for low-speed transportation</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
